name: Costa Coffee
directions: On the ground floor, opposite the tills, to the right of the stairs.

name: Róisín
directions: At the back of the shop.
comment: Can use even if you don’t buy anything

name: Joann Fabric and Crafts
directions: In the back of the store.
comment: Available to the public.

name: Gloucester County Institute of Technology
directions: 200 wing of the building

name: Nick's Deli
directions: It is at the back left of the store but is not marked for the public. You can also just ask the person behind the store counter or the deli counter.
comment:
This is not marked for a public restroom but the store will let you go. The store is wheelchair accessible but the back room is a little tight. 
This is a minority family business and they are very supportive of the rest of us.

name: Landmark Café & Crêperie
directions: In the back by the kitchen. Signs say gender neutral.

name: East Carolina University - Old Cafeteria Complex
directions: Enter Old Cafeteria Complex from the back entrance facing Joyner Library. As soon as you walk in the double doors, there is a door on the right side labeled G-101. In that area are two single-use restrooms that are also handicap accessible.
comment: The building is open from 8am to 5pm Monday through Friday, mainly for ECU-affiliated personnel.

name: Amy & Co
directions: Walk past the register towards the curtain, before the curtain it's the door on the left.
comment: Large single toilet restroom, with a lock on the door.

name: Apple Pie Store and Bakery
comment: This is for paying customers only. There is one disabled one that is fully accessible (key provided upon request) - this is a gender neutral toilet. There is also another gender neutral toilet downstairs.

name: Anythink Brighton Library
directions: 3 Options- Mens and Womens near the front entrance (west side of the building) and two single restrooms, one in the back near the computer lab (far east end of the building) and one in the kids room (north side of the building, you can access it through the garden entrance). The kids room one is tucked into the north west corner of the space and has a changing table.
comment: Open to the public, no need to have a library card or be from the area to use. Also has free wifi and computer access.

name: Target
directions: An immediate right turn after entering the building.
comment: You can enter whichever bathroom you identify/ are more comfortable with!

name: The Crepery
directions: behind the counter, past the soda fountain, in the hallway

name: Have a Gay Day
directions: in the back of the office space

name: KB HALLEN
directions: Next to dressing rooms
comment: Lovely restroom with genderneutral sign on doors, welcoming all.

name: Beach Side Cafe at Sand Castle
directions: By the pool
comment: You do have to be a paying customer.

name: Castaway's
directions: When you walk in the restroom is the first door on the right side.

name: Goldfish Swim School
directions: At the end of the hall by the back door there are four single stall bathrooms. Two are labeled men and two are labeled women, but they all have a sink, toilet, and changing table and many people (staff and guests alike) use any of them regardless of signs.
comment: There is a back door up a flight of stairs and a front door on sidewalk level. If you enter through the front you will pass the front desk but don't need to prove yourself or buy anything.

name: SpaceCraft Brewery
directions: On the left side of the bar

name: Brodie Resource Library
directions: Ground floor in the children's department, to the left of the desk when you come down the main stairs, labelled the family washroom.
comment: Door will state it is the family washroom. The door will be locked, you will need to ask staff for the key, stating that you need use of the safe washroom.

name: Shoe's Cup and Cork
directions: Main entrance to the right of counter
comment: Bathroom is for outside and indoor seating, generally no questions asked.

name: Danville Area Community College
directions: Each building on the DACC campus has bathrooms specifically dedicated as gender-neutral and single user.
comment: Available to anyone visiting the campus.

name: Realm Library
directions: Second floor, by the elevators. Bathrooms and adult changing space with shower.
comment: Totally free, part of library/council services. Library staff are wonderful and inclusive.

name: Lincoln-Tallman House, Rock County Historical Society
directions: Northwest corner, first floor. May have to take the stairs from the front entrance.
comment: There is *technically* an elevator for wheelchair use to make them accessible, however I noted from the outside there area couple small steps.

name: Trinity College Dublin Lloyd Building
directions: Enter the front door of the Lloyd, turn right, through the door and the bathroom is on your right (opposite the elevator)
comment: You might have to be a student but IDS are never checked.

name: Searles Leisure Resoirt
directions: Accessible toilet near entrance to Sundowner Lounge
comment: Key available from the bar if you do not have a radar key.

name: Henry's Restaurant and Grill
directions: Towards the back

name: Walmart
directions: Back of the store

name: Save on foods
directions: Next to the deli in a short hallway.
comment: It's a single unisex room.

name: Flamingos Coffee House
directions: Right hand side of the bar
comment: LGBT+ coffee house, super friendly and has a whole accessibility document on their website

name: War Memorial Library
directions: Ground floor at the Little Theatre end of the building

name: Webster Hall
directions: Basement of venue

name: Westside YMCA
directions: Use the Family Locker Room. The bathrooms are unisex, accessible, and single stall. Single stall changing rooms are also available.
comment: You need to be a member, but you can use a guest pass three times per year to try out the gym. Bring ID.

name: Giant Eagle
directions: In the middle along the back wall of the store
comment: Do not need to be a paying customer.

name: Mr. Mesquite Taqueria
directions: Follow hallway straight back passed order counter
comment: Must be paying customer, employees give you key code

name: Ding Tea
comment: Have to be paying customer. Ask employees for access. Asked employees to confirm it was a trans safe place

name: Boulders On Broadway
directions: To the left when you walk in. Hallway with 4 single stalls with communal sinks towards end of the hall. Changing table near sinks
comment: Bar and staff don't have a clear eyeline to the bathrooms so you can easily dip in and out if needed.

name: Dawn Myers
directions: Bathrooms are to the right when you first walk in and bathrooms in the back of the store by the pets section

name: Kenji's Ramen and Grill
directions: Near back of restaurant

name: AHBL Building
directions: Available Wednesday & Thursday, ask for Dr Gorny
comment: Two available, bathroom doors have key access, ask at Bayview Eyecare

name: Ikea Innaloo
street: 6 Sunray Drive off, Ellen Stirling Blvd
directions: 1 lot on the first floor (turn left after you went up the escalator), 2nd one is on the second floor (turn left and take the short cut to the restaurant and follow the signs from there)

name: Melbourne Law School
directions: Different toilets on multiple floors
comment: Act like you belong at school I guess?

name: Jackass Charm
directions: Right across from front door
comment: Welcoming place and ownership. Safe for all!

name: Vanderbilt University - Peabody College, Administration Building
directions: There are two of them, side by side, on the first floor, by the front door of the building, in front of the Career Center offices.
comment: Building may be closed on the weekends, but is open during the week.  Building is wheelchair accessible, these specific bathrooms are not.

name: Cotixan
directions: Single bathrooms
comment: Get token from cashier

name: Dana Downs
directions: To the back on the righthand side
comment: The pin for this Chipotle is currently located on the map where the Whataburger is and needs to be moved

name: Cat'sEye Wine Bar
directions: In the back, there's a ramp if needed
comment: Single stall rooms, and the gender pictures are birds, so feel free to interpret which one represents you!

name: South Central Community Action Partners
directions: Enter in the front of the building, ask the receptionist for the closest restroom and you can be accommodated to either a family gender neutral room or a gendered safe space room. All restrooms have locks on the doors for privacy.

name: Kaiser Permanente Salmon Creek
directions: 1st floor By elevators on the left of entry

name: Central Lutheran Church
directions: Single Stalls on main floor and balcony level. Gender neutral with toilets and urinal on lower level. Gendered and safe bathrooms on main level, both with changing tables and both stocked with menstrual supplies.

name: Aldi
directions: Front of store behind the registers. 2 single stall restrooms.

name: Paul Mitchell The School
comment: Only available for staff and students, has signage signifying it is safe for all genders, multiple restrooms in this facility are labeled as such

name: IMC Oranmore
directions: Up the elevator, through the wide double doors
comment: You don’t have to be a paying customer, staff are friendly.

name: University of Guelph
directions: UC has multiple gender neutral washrooms, including on the first floor just on the left when you enter. There is also a gender neutral ('universal') change room at the athletic centre
comment: Don't have to be a student to use them. There are more gender neutral bathrooms on others floors and in other UofG buildings. List: https://www.uoguelph.ca/studentexperience/system/files/02.21.20_Gender%20Neutral%20Bathrooms%20Web%20Draft.pdf

name: Bob Evans
directions: Straight through the front door to the bathrooms.  On the far right.
comment: This is a "Family" restroom. I would assume they expect only paying customers to use the bathroom.

name: 4550 US-287, Hedley, TX 79237, USA
directions: Outside bathrooms for both genders large enough to be accommodating.
comment: I had no problems with using the ladies room. Most go inside the main building to use facilities.

name: Providence St. Mary Medical Center
directions: There are several bathrooms throughout the hospital but the one listed here is near ICU B.
comment: Due to covid-19 you must wear a mask even if vaccinated

name: Mischief Toys
directions: Main floor - toward the back
comment: All are welcome

name: Morgenstern's Bookstore & Café
directions: 2 large, single stall bathrooms in the back of the store.

name: Camp Augusta
directions: Community Room, staff house, and lodge all have single stall neutral restrooms
comment: You have to be a staff member, camper, family camper, or group member, but if you are planning to come here, dont worry the bathroom situation has some options outside of just gendered bathhouses

name: Tim Horton's
directions: Right pass exit door, 2 washrooms, well maintained.
comment: I work there an I am willing to personally protect the right of anyone needing to use the washroom.

name: Community College of Aurora
directions: Two single stall, gender neutral bathrooms available in the Fine Arts Building.
comment: Available when campus is open. See ccaurora.edu for hours.

name: Starbucks
comment: Two separate single-stall unisex bathrooms. Large enough to accommodate a wheelchair. Changing tables and handrails in both. Doors are manual.

name: Snug Harbor
comment: Open friendly atmosphere

name: Starbucks
directions: It's right in front of the store.
comment: You need a code, but the baristas give it to you right away.

name: Scale & Feather Meadery
street: 1050 N Fairway Dr Building E, Suite 112

name: Funko Hollywood
directions: Two handicap accessible gendered stalls with changing tables and then single stalls that are non gendered.
comment: For customers only.

name: Four Generals Brewing
directions: Walk past the bar all the way to the 1924 iron jail door in the back. All ages may come in.
comment: Just say refuge restroom at the bar. I own this place and you are very welcome to use the facilities.

name: Nopa
directions: In the back towards the kitchen
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: New Belgium Brewing Taproom & Restaurant
directions: Beyond the bar along the side of the building facing Mission Bay Creek
comment: You might need to be a paying customer but highly recommend the Blackberry Black Tea Sour & the Voodoo Fries. Also I could be wrong about the changing tables. I didn't see a changing table in the stalls though.

name: 926 Bar & Grill
directions: There are two bathrooms on the “pub side,” one is an accessible large bathroom, the other has two very small stalls. On the “club side,” there is a bathroom with 3 stalls including one handicapped stall. The bathrooms are at the back of the club side, by the bar. If needed, there is a ramp behind the DJ booth.
comment: This is a gay bar, and one of the most welcoming and inclusive places in Tallahassee. If you ever have an issue with anyone, let a staff member know and they’ll help you to safety if needed.

name: Glen Site MUHC
directions: On the main floor, next to the security desk

name: Chemistry Building
directions:
Education building level 1 ED. 1047
Business building level 1 BN. 1012B
Earth Sciences building level 1 ER 1004
University Center level 6 UC6018 & 6026

name: Second Cup Boulevard Gréber
directions: At the end of the café (close to the front counters), there is a small hallway. They are two usually available, but one is currently only for employees due to COVID.
comment: The owner is very friendly and welcoming! He is also a veteran from the Canadian Army and helps the community by hiring people with disabilities :)

name: Adventure Gaming Store
directions: In the back room, just ask to use the rest room.

name: Home Depot
directions: Once inside, turn left, go all the way to the wall, there's a small hallway with multiple bathrooms, one of which is unisex, and locks with a red button near the toilet.
comment: HD is very inclusive and welcomes all.

name: Common Market
directions: Right across from the main registers.
comment: This establishment made their bathrooms gender neutral as soon as North Carolina’s “Bathroom Bill” passed. They are extremely supportive of trans rights. This is a safe space for any person experiencing issues, just let a member of the staff know.

name: Starbucks - Monroe Market Place
directions: To the right when entering through main door. 2 different single stall unisex bathrooms

name: Ursa Minor Brewing
comment: Two of the 3 bathrooms are accessible

name: RareTea
directions: I’m back of store to the left past the “office”
comment: Bathroom is for customers only

name: Requiem Coffee Tea and Fantasy
directions: Enter through the front entrance. Restrooms are located near the cashier station.
comment: Very inclusive coffee shop!

name: Planet Diner
directions: At the back of the restaurant
comment: Very LGBTQ2+ friendly

name: Pure Pizza
comment: Check out the posted sign explaining the need for gender neutral restrooms
